I Love the Sci-fi Shipyards mod, being a Trekker at heart. Since I upgraded to [0.90] I've been patiently waiting for updated mod. Any idea when Shipyards will be available for the new Kerbal Space Version? I really miss the Enterprise and my favorite, The Phoenix.

Keith

It seems to be working in .90 for me. I've been using it since .90 was released.
I should hope an expansion is planned for more trek ships... please.

I put together this KAS patch (needs Module Manager as well) so that the flags that come this pack can be grabbed, stored, and attached to things (both structures and the ground):


@PART[folding_flag]:NEEDS[KAS]
{
    MODULE
    {
        name = KASModuleGrab
        evaPartPos = (0.0, 0.0, -0.14)
        evaPartDir = (0,0,-1)
        storable = true
        storedSize = 2
        attachOnPart = True
        attachOnEva = True
        attachOnStatic = True
        attachSendMsgOnly = False
    }
}
Its just a "parts mod", it doesn't require to be updated.
May I have the source model files please? I would like to add RCS ports to the Enterprise.
do I need anything for this?
Which pack is the TARDIS in? all i want is the TARDIS. Does it still work?

I just started going though the mod a couple of nights ago, and everything seems to be working okay, just a lot of memory issues. One things I've done is gone through most of the textures and converted them to mbm. This should prevent the issue where some parts are solid white when lit up, as well as give a better estimate on how the textures will affect the RAM.

Another thing I've done since last release was re-doing the Phoenix. It's mostly done, I just need to create the internal for it. For now I'll just update the mod and remove the Phoenix, then add it back in later. If you want the old Phoenix I'll put up a download in the original post. I've also added RCS to the Enterprise.

The Phoenix looks something like this right now. This is an old render, but not much as changed.

Is there any way to ad the Warp Drive from the Interstellar mod to these ships?

I can't think of an elegant way to do it, and they are mostly way too big anyway. That said, with a bit of practise, you can zip between the planets pretty much by targeting at them and flying straight at them. Orbiting can be tricky, but I've had fun with it.

One request though, maybe it can be done by editing, would be for the TARDIS sound effects to be mapped to the thruster. As it is, the noise gets on the nerves, running even when the engines aren't running. Anyone know how to fix it? (Apart from turning the engine off through the right click menu)

The module manager patches in the download should already add Warp Drives to the ships if you have interstellar. Then again, they weren't tested very thoroughly.

thrustAddedToPitch = 0

just switch the values around.
